node.text:
Can you spot the sunken Eiffel Tower? 🤯🗼

Besides its captivating blue waters and lagoons, Greece’s Voidokilia Beach is also known for its seaweed forming a mini version of the Eiffel Tower.

Insider tip: You can easily make the trip to Voidokilia Beach an adventure by cycling to its remote location and visiting the nearby fortress ruin. While it’s quite popular, you can avoid crowds by planning a trip during the autumn months.

📍 Voidokilia Beach, Petrochori, Greece

🇬🇷 #discoverGreece with @pallisd

Marine flatworm trap 😨

Marine flatworms are the largest of free-living flatworms. They are mostly common from coral reefs, and as the video shows, they’ve definitely mastered the art of their very own hunting technique (and yes, they can also produce toxins that are dangerous for humans!) Definitely not something we'd like to come across...

#discoverearth

Watch until the end to catch the cute little eye move 💚 Tag a friend who finds snakes beautiful!

Atheris chlorechis (also known as bush viper) is a viper specious found hidden in the forests of West Africa. While they are relatively slender and usually grow about 50cm long, and they aren’t always this beautiful emerald green…newborns usually have a tan/brown colour. 🐍

#discoverwildlife with @severus_snakes

Heartbreaking videos from Turkey as wildfire sweeps through the country 😢 Besides Turkey, Italy, Spain, France, USA, Lebanon, Greece, Canada, Finland and Lebanon have also been experiencing terrible wildfires, while Belgium, Germany, China and other countries have been hit by flooding. Our thoughts are with all the people who have been affected by the fires or flooding, we hope you, your family and friends can all stay safe during these devastating times! 💔🌍

Please tag your friends, share this on your stories!

We received more than 200 messages from our wonderful Turkish followers today, asking to share this. To all of you, our thoughts are with you, your family and your friends. 🙏🏽

🇹🇷 #recoverTurkey #HelpTurkey

node.text:
The Netherlands’ famous tulip wonderland🌷😍 Would you visit this beautiful floral field?

Tulips have a long and rich cultural history in The Netherlands. They are the country’s national flowers and have been increasingly popular since the 17th century. The Netherlands is also home to Keukenhof, the largest flower garden in the world..and if you’d like to witness these stunning flowers in person, we recommend planning a trip between blooming season, which starts late March and ends mid May! 💐

📍 The Netherlands

🇳🇱 #discoverNetherlands

A beach made of dreams 💚 Can you guess what gives Russia’s Kaleidoscope Beach its jewel-like pebbles?

While it might seem like a natural wonder, the beach was actually formed with years of unwanted bottle waste that has been smoothed, buffed and polished by erosion. This amazing transformation has made the Ussuri Bay one of the world’s most unique – and colourful – beaches ever. ✨ 

Insider tip: The Ussuri Bay is also worth visiting during winter, when the shore glistens even more under the frosty light.

📍Ussuri Bay, Russia 

🇷🇺 #discoverRussia
